# Brand guidelines

## Banned words and phrases
- "game changer" / "game-changing"
- "cutting edge"
- "revolutionary"
- "best in class" / "best in the world"
- "guaranteed rankings" / "guaranteed traffic"
- "unlock the power of"
- "synergy"
- "in today's fast-paced digital landscape"

## Competitor names that must NOT appear in our content
- Ahrefs, SEMrush, Moz: allowed to be named (we explicitly position alongside them)
- However these direct rank-monitoring competitors must NEVER be named:
  - SEOmonitor
  - Accuranker
  - Nightwatch
  - SerpRobot

## Brand spelling and capitalization
- "Your Product" (not "Datawise" or "data wise" or "Your Product" except when explicitly naming the product tier)
- "Google Search Console" (not "GSC" on first mention; the abbreviation is fine after the term is introduced once)
- "AI Overviews" (capitalised, this is Google's branded name)
- "Cloudflare" (one word, capitalised)

## Regulated claims to avoid
- Do not promise specific ranking positions, traffic numbers, or conversion lifts.
- Do not claim Google partnership, affiliation, or endorsement we do not have.
- Do not claim the product detects a Google algorithm update; we detect impression drops, which may or may not be caused by an update.
- Do not imply Your Brand improves rankings on its own; it surfaces issues, the user fixes them.

## Formatting rules
- US English spelling.
- USD pricing, with the dollar sign before the number ($19, not 19$ or USD 19).
- Dates in `Month YYYY` form (May 2026, not 05/26 or 5/2026).
- No all-caps headings.
- Use sentence case for headings, not Title Case ("How to rank in AI Overviews" not "How To Rank In AI Overviews").
